TITLE: Requesting Quote with Platform Fee in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to request a quote from the Jupiter Swap API with a platform fee of 20 basis points (0.2%). It uses the fetch API to make a GET request to the quote endpoint.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jup-ag/docs/blob/main/docs/100-swap-api/4-add-fees-to-swap.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
const quoteResponse = await (
    await fetch(
        'https://lite-api.jup.ag/swap/v1/quote?inputMint=So11111111111111111111111111111111111111112&outputMint=EPjFWdd5AufqSSqeM2qN1xzybapC8G4wEGGkZwyTDt1v&amount=100000&slippageBps=50&restrictIntermediateTokens=true&platformFeeBps=20'
    )
  ).json();

console.log(JSON.stringify(quoteResponse, null, 2));
```

